Rating: 4
I made this for our New Year's Eve party and they disappeared! It was very easy to prepare. Instead of making the spiced nuts, I used prepared candied pecans, added a dash of cayenne and then chopped them. If you usually like creamier blue cheeses (such as Maytag Blue), I suggest using a blue that is a little sharper for this dish. It goes perfectly with the sweet-salty nuts and honey and the slight bitterness of the endive.

